parameters: Nakano: I'm sorry, \P[0001]-kun, but I'm busy today.
Nakano: Please come again next time.
Nakano: Hehe... Aki is not here.
Hinata Aki: Hey Nakano-san, are you free today...?
Nakano: Hey hey, Aki, \P[0001]-kun is here right now, you know?

Hinata Aki: ...\P[0001]... Is something wrong? Do you have
something to talk to Nakano-san about?
Hinata Aki: Nakano-san, I was surprised! I can't move outside.

Nakano: I was planning to go shopping, but I can't move as I
wanted...
Nakano: It's difficult to live alone at this age, huh.

Hinata Aki: Nakano-san, you shouldn't push yourself if your back
hurts.
Nakano: I'm sorry... I showed you such a pathetic side.
Hinata Aki: There's nothing pathetic about it.

Hinata Aki: That's right! If Nakano-san has any troubles, feel
free to tell me anything.
Hinata Aki: If there's anything I can do, I'll help you!

Nakano: It's not that bad... Besides, you must be busy with your
studies, right?

Hinata Aki: I-I'm... I'll be fine! I'll figure something out!...
Probably

Nakano: I see... Well, then maybe I'll rely on you when I'm in
trouble.
Hinata Aki: Yeah! Leave it to me!
Nakano: I can't let this opportunity slip away... <K♥>
Nakano: I'm sorry for being busy again today.
Hinata Aki: Hmm! It's totally fine.

Hinata Aki: By the way, Nakano-san's house is full of books,
isn't it?

Hinata Aki: Are books interesting...? When there are only words,
I get sleepy.

Nakano: It's interesting~ It's like imagining and reliving the
author's experiences through words, I guess~
Nakano: As someone who lives alone, it fills the loneliness.

Nakano: I feel like it's not an exaggeration to say that it's my
reason for living~
Hinata Aki: Chosha...? Tsuitaiken...? It seems difficult, but...
Hinata Aki: If it's fun for Nakano-san, then it's okay!
Nakano: Oh, I have a book recommendation for you, Aki- chan.
Nakano: Yeah, yeah, I had it around there...

Hinata Aki: Hey hey! Don't push yourself, Nakano-san. I'll look
for it.

Nakano: I wonder if there's a good book... I really wanted to
give it as a present.

Nakano: Sorry, it would be great if you could find it
yourself...
Nakano: My back hurts and I can't bend down.
Hinata Aki: No, don't worry about it.
Hinata Aki: I'm curious about the book you recommend for me.
Hinata Aki: Ah! Is this it?

Hinata Aki: The charm of older men... Be careful around men
